Here's the complete step-by-step implementation guide, in exact order.

Phase 1 — Firebase Setup
Step 1 — Create the project

Go to console.firebase.google.com
Click "Add project"
Name it ipl-fantasy-league → click Continue
Toggle off Google Analytics → click Create project
Wait ~10 seconds → click Continue

Step 2 — Create the Firestore database

In the left sidebar → click Build → Firestore Database
Click "Create database"
Select "Start in test mode" → click Next
Region: select asia-south1 (Mumbai) → click Enable
Wait for it to finish — you'll see an empty database screen

Step 3 — Fix the security rules

Inside Firestore, click the "Rules" tab at the top
Delete everything in the editor and paste this:

rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /{document=**} {
      allow read, write: if true;
    }
  }
}

Click "Publish"

Step 4 — Get your Firebase config

Click the gear icon ⚙️ (top left, next to "Project Overview") → Project settings
Scroll down to "Your apps" section
Click the </> Web icon
Nickname: type anything (e.g. ipl-web) → click "Register app"
You'll see a code block — copy these 6 values and keep them somewhere:

apiKey
authDomain
projectId
storageBucket
messagingSenderId
appId

Phase 2 — Configure the HTML File
Step 5 — Edit the file

Download ipl-fantasy-v4.html
Open it in a text editor

Windows: right-click → Open with → Notepad
Mac: right-click → Open with → TextEdit → then Format → Make Plain Text
Recommended: VS Code if you have it


At the very top of the <script> block, find this section:

jsconst FIREBASE_CONFIG = {
  apiKey:            "REPLACE_apiKey",
  authDomain:        "REPLACE_authDomain",
  projectId:         "REPLACE_projectId",
  storageBucket:     "REPLACE_storageBucket",
  messagingSenderId: "REPLACE_messagingSenderId",
  appId:             "REPLACE_appId"
};

Replace each REPLACE_* with your actual values from Step 4
Save the file (Ctrl+S on Windows, Cmd+S on Mac)


Phase 3 — Deploy
Step 6 — Deploy to Netlify

Go to app.netlify.com/drop
Drag and drop your saved ipl-fantasy-v4.html file onto the page
Wait ~5 seconds — you'll get a live URL like sunny-dolphin-abc123.netlify.app
Open that URL — you should see the IPL Fantasy login screen
Optional: click "Site configuration" → "Change site name" to get something like sai-ipl-fantasy.netlify.app


✅ If you see the login screen, Firebase is connected and working.


Phase 4 — First Time Admin Setup
Step 7 — Log in as admin

Open your Netlify URL
Click "Admin" tab on the login screen
Enter PIN: 0000 (the default)
You're in the admin panel

Step 8 — Change your admin PIN

Go to League Setup tab (top right of admin panel)
In the Admin PIN field, replace 0000 with your own 4-digit PIN
Click Save
Remember this PIN — it's the only way back into the admin panel

Step 9 — Generate the join link

Still in the League Setup tab
Click "Generate Join Link"
You'll see a 6-character code like IPL4X7 and a full link
Click Copy
Send this link to your friends on WhatsApp — this is how they register


Phase 5 — Get Cricket API Key
Step 10 — Sign up for CricketData.org

Go to cricketdata.org
Click Sign Up — free, no credit card needed
Verify your email
Log in → go to your Dashboard
Copy your API key

Step 11 — Save the API key in the app

Go to admin panel → Current Match tab
In the CricketAPI section, paste your API key into the field
Click "Save Key"


Phase 6 — GitHub
Step 12 — Create the repository

Go to github.com → click "New" (green button)
Repository name: ipl-fantasy-league
Set visibility to Private ← important, your Firebase keys are in the HTML file
Leave everything else as default → click "Create repository"

Step 13 — Push the files
Open a terminal in the folder where your files are and run:
bashgit init
git add ipl-fantasy-v4.html README.md
git commit -m "Initial commit — IPL Fantasy League v4"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ipl-fantasy-league.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
Replace YOUR_USERNAME with your actual GitHub username.

Phase 7 — Match Day Flow
Step 14 — Morning of the match

Log into admin panel
Go to Current Match tab
Fill in Match Label (e.g. MI vs CSK — Match 1) and the two team names
Click "+ Create New Match"
Click "Find IPL Matches" → select today's match from the list
Playing XI auto-loads into the player pool
Share the league URL with your friends so they can pick their teams

Step 15 — Before toss (~30 min)

Check that everyone has submitted — you'll see ✓ next to each name in the submissions list
Click "🔒 Lock Teams" → confirm
No one can edit their team after this

Step 16 — At the toss

The moment the toss is announced on TV, click "🥁 TOSS DONE — REVEAL!" → confirm
Everyone's screen instantly flips to the leaderboard showing all teams

Step 17 — During the match

Go to Player Stats tab
Select 5 min from the auto-refresh dropdown
Click the ⏸ OFF button — it turns 🟢 ON
Stats fetch automatically every 5 minutes and points update live for everyone
After each innings, manually check and fix any missing catches, stumpings, or run-outs

Step 18 — After the match

Click "⚡ Fetch Now" one final time for complete stats
Manually fix any fielding stats the API missed
Click "✅ Finalize & Save to Season" → confirm
Points are permanently saved to the season leaderboard
Click "+ Start Next Match" when you're ready for the next game


